2.2 Manual installation
=======================

Assuming your Emacs files are found in ‚Äò~/.emacs.d/‚Äô, execute the
following commands in a shell prompt:

     cd ~/.emacs.d

     # Create a directory for manually-installed packages
     mkdir manual-packages

     # Go to the new directory
     cd manual-packages

     # Clone this repo, naming it "notmuch-indicator"
     git clone https://github.com/protesilaos/notmuch-indicator notmuch-indicator

   Finally, in your ‚Äòinit.el‚Äô (or equivalent) evaluate this:

     ;; Make Elisp files in that directory available to the user.
     (add-to-list 'load-path "~/.emacs.d/manual-packages/notmuch-indicator")

   Everything is in place to set up the package.


